blocks.name: cttg
blocks.content: Function to convert an algebraic structure to a Tarski geometry.

blocks.name: df-ttg
blocks.content: Define a function converting a subcomplex Hilbert space to a Tarski Geometry. It does so by equipping the structure with a betweenness operation. Note that because the scalar product is applied over the interval ` ( 0 [,] 1 ) ` , only spaces whose scalar field is a superset of that interval can be considered. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 24-Mar-2019.)
